                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Finland/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kagey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsingfors</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-06T18:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 6, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 6—noon.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Referring to the Department’s circular through Paris, April 21, noon. Finnish
                    Minister at Washington has been instructed to negotiate with World War Foreign
                    Debt Commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kagey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
